{
  "text": "The most commonly used approach to model the effect of covariates on survival probabilities is the Cox Proportional Hazards Model, [CITATION_1] . The major theoretical development that this model provides is the ability to model covariate effects in the presence of censored observations.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "116197768"
